714215f-a.title: Manhattan: 67th Street (West) - Columbus Avenue
714215f-a.text:
42-50 West 67th Street, south side, between Columbus avenue
and Central Park West.
About 1923.
Maximilian J. Jahelka.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

719075f-a.title: Manhattan: Columbus Avenue - 67th Street (West)
719075f-a.text:
Columbus Ave., north from but not including West 67th Street, showing the
roadbed prior to street car track removal by the W.P.A. Overhead is the
Ninth Ave. Elevated Line.
August 25, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

719076f-b.title: Manhattan: Columbus Avenue - 67th Street (West)
719076f-b.text:
Columbus Avenue, north from W,st 67th Street as photographed
from the express platform of the 66th Streeet station on the 9th
Avenue ''gl'' line. The open space at the left is the block site
upon which the former 1st Field Artillery Armory stood. This ex-
tends from 67th to 68th Streets, Columbus Avenue to Broadway.
June 26, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
